Dcl commands in sql
Data Control Language (DCL) commands in SQL are used to control access to data in a database. The two main DCL commands are:
1. GRANT: This command is used to give specific privileges to users or roles. For example, you can grant SELECT, INSERT, UPDATE, or DELETE permissions on a table to a user.
2. REVOKE: This command is used to remove previously granted privileges from users or roles. For example, you can revoke SELECT permission from a user on a specific table.
eg:
```sql-- Grant SELECT permission on the Employees table to user 'john'
GRANT SELECT ON Employees TO john;  
-- Revoke SELECT permission on the Employees table from user 'john'
REVOKE SELECT ON Employees FROM john;
```